The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Pune, Oct. 12 (PTI): Rashtrapati Bhavan has received an email threat against President Pratibha Patil.          
	Officials said the mail addressed to Patil, now in Pune, warns of attackers coming in any disguise. It reportedly uses words like doomed and damned country. Intelligence agencies and police have been alerted.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The connections of 10,151 phones of telemarketers will be snapped for repeated violation of Do Not Call registry norms, telecom regulator Trai has said. But officials added that the number of unsolicited calls to subscribers to the Do Not Call registry has fallen.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The railways will introduce coaches with greater seating capacity, a senior ministry official said. The manufacturing cost of the new stainless steel coaches will also be lower, the official said.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The National Human Rights Commission on Sunday recommended that undertrials be allowed to vote. It also said the maximum period of detention should be fixed at six months.                                                                                                                          
